-- Turkey Plans to Drop State Monopoly on Railroads, Sabah Reports
-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 2012-05-28T08:21:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/turkey-plans-to-drop-state-monopoly-on-railroads-sabah-reports.html
Turkey ’s government is drafting a
proposal that would drop the state’s monopoly on railroads,
Sabah  cited  Transportation Minister Binali Yildirim as saying.  The revisions will enable investors to build new rail lines
and purchase licenses to run existing parts of the network,
Yildirim told reporters in Milan, according to the Istanbul-
based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in Ankara at 
 epeker2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
